{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"Volume","externalID":"s:3GIO6VolumeC","symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Volume"}],"roleHeading":"Class","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Volume","kind":"identifier"}]},"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GVolume","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" interface represents user-visible objects that can be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"mounted. For example, a file system partition on a USB flash drive, or an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"optical disc inserted into a disc drive.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(_:)-19lze","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(_:)-22yto","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(_:)-90d3j","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(_:)-i1m7","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(_:)-ru3","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(raw:)-5hn7m","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(raw:)-9aa0v","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(retainingRaw:)-8j8bx","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(retainingRaw:)-8ufgk"],"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/metatypeReferenceForVolume","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/ptr","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/wrapperForVolume"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Type Properties","anchor":"Type-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/metatypeForVolume"]},{"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/VolumeProtocol-Implementations"]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/VolumeProtocol"],"title":"Conforms To"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Volume"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GVolume","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is currently mounted, the corresponding [iface"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Mount","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be retrieved using [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Volume.get_mount"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mounting a "},{"code":"GVolume","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance is an asynchronous operation. For more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"information about asynchronous operations, see [iface"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"] and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Task"},{"type":"text","text":"]. To mount a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVolume"},{"type":"text","text":", first call [method"},{"code":"Gio.Volume.mount","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with (at least) the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVolume"},{"text":" instance, optionally a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MountOperation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] object and a [type"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncReadyCallback","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically, one will only want to pass "},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MountOperation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] if automounting all volumes when a desktop session"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"starts since it’s not desirable to put up a lot of dialogs asking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for credentials."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The callback will be fired when the operation has resolved (either"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with success or failure), and a [iface"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] instance will be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed to the callback.  That callback should then call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Volume.mount_finish"},{"text":"] with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVolume"},{"text":" instance and the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[iface"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] data to see if the operation was completed"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"successfully.  If a [type[GLibError](\/\/documentation\/glib\/gliberror] is present when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.Volume.mount_finish","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] is called, then it will be filled with any","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"error information."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note, when ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"migrating-gnome-vfs.html"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVolume"},{"type":"text","text":" is the moral equivalent of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GnomeVFSDrive"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Volume Identifiers","anchor":"Volume-Identifiers","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is sometimes necessary to directly access the underlying"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"operating system object behind a volume (e.g. for passing a volume"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to an application via the command line). For this purpose, GIO"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"allows to obtain an ‘identifier’ for the volume. There can be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"different kinds of identifiers, such as Hal UDIs, filesystem labels,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"traditional Unix devices (e.g. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/dev\/sda2"},{"type":"text","text":"), UUIDs. GIO uses predefined"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strings as names for the different kinds of identifiers:"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VOLUME_IDENTIFIER_KIND_UUID"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"G_VOLUME_IDENTIFIER_KIND_LABEL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", etc."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use [method"},{"code":"Gio.Volume.get_identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] to obtain an identifier for a volume."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VOLUME_IDENTIFIER_KIND_HAL_UDI"},{"text":" will only be available","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"when the GVFS hal volume monitor is in use. Other volume monitors","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will generally be able to provide the "},{"code":"G_VOLUME_IDENTIFIER_KIND_UNIX_DEVICE","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identifier, which can be used to obtain a hal device by means of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"libhal_manager_find_device_string_match()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVolume"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/VolumeProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVolume"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/VolumeRef"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVolume"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/volume"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Volume/init(gconstpointer:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(gconstpointer:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Optional initialiser from a non-mutating "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gconstpointer"},{"text":" to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the underlying "},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" data type.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This creates an instance without performing an unbalanced retain"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"i.e., ownership is transferred to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"init(gconstpointer:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/volume\/init(gconstpointer:)","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"!(","kind":"text"},{"text":"gconstpointer","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gconstpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gconstpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Volume/init(cPointer:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Volume\/init(cPointer:)","type":